column1:
This crazy summer's given us a whole lotta grief,
but our mission was a success, and we made a
buncha great memories together, so...

What's wrong, Ryuji? You don't appear to be
your usual self.

Man, I could NOT fall asleep last night...
My bed at home just wasn't doin' it for me.

I gotcha. Our bodies are all specced for the
Feathermobile at this point.
I find myself missing the Feathermobile too.

Why'd ya change the name when we don't even
got it anymore?
That was true—at least, for a little while...

Anyway, it looks like nobody besides us Thieves
remembers what happened at the Tokyo Radio
Tower, just like last time.

*sigh* That sucks, considering it was our asses
on the line an' all...

Patrolling society from the shadows, slaying
evil in secret? I admit it sounds rather alluring.

Well yeah, but don'tcha want some kinda
recognition every once in a while, too?
Y'know, like... fangirls and that kinda stuff?
I get enough of that already.
Eeeee! Joker! Skull! You're sooo cool!
Not you! And your actin's awful!

Screw you! Mister Superstar over here...
The girls in your hometown prolly go
crazy for ya, don't they?

Still, we made all sorts of unforgettable
memories. I couldn't have asked for
anything more.

Same here. It was a new experience at every
turn. It was the best.

Mmhm, and we can rest easy knowing we did
everything we could to help. Any loose strings
left are in the middle of being wrapped up.

Man, Gramps woulda really helped
to turn this party up, huh?

I bet he'd say he's too busy trying to bring in
Owada to attend a celebration just yet.

So we're all partyin' while Zenkichi's still
bustin' his buns on the case? Now I'm
feelin' a bit guilty...

Maybe because you remembered school's
starting back up soon? And doesn't that go
for all of you?

Oh! Yeah, that reminds me—when're ya headin'
home, [1B]S1?
Well, duh, man! And make it soon, 'kay?

Hmmm, me too... Make like a perennial and
be sure you come back, okay?

Hoo boy... Good thing [1B]S1's got me
after all, huh?
Sophia, will you be joining them?

And what if she ends up sniffin' out a Jail in
his hometown, huh?

Now that you mention it, I wonder why Sophia
was in the Shibuya Jail anyway, of all places...

Well, Ichinose did mention that she used to
live in Shibuya.

Perhaps Sophia was originally located within
her house.

So when EMMA picked up on Sophia's
existence from the Metaverse side, that
cognition...

Ah, this is all speculation. And even if that's
how any of it worked, it'd have to be some
sort of miracle.

Since we're on the topic... Sophia, you seemed
a bit distracted after we defeated the Demiurge.
Did something happen?
You mean the one only you can hear?
Yes. I was issued a final request...
"Please follow your heart to save humanity."

Had we been able to reach a mutual agreement,
perhaps EMMA could have followed Sophia's
path rather than face destruction...

I believe this is proof of the true power that the
Phantom Thieves hold.

Artificial intelligence is not the enemy of
mankind. We were born to help people.

But, just like people, we are capable of errors
in judgment and can stray from the right path.

Our users, their input, our experience—these
all mold us to take a wide variety of beliefs.

If only EMMA had learned and grown with a
good companion...

Then why don't you give yourself the directive
to show others how it's done?

Since you're such a good companion to
humanity, you can be a positive role model
for how AI and humans can work together.

I couldn't even count how many people that'd
end up helping in the end.
Oh—but, I can't leave this smartphone.

That's a shame. Being a role model and helping
countless people will have to wait.

Mweheheheh... Not so fast, Sophia! I've cooked
up an ultra-epic—

Argh, shut up, shut up, shut up! This is
gettin' TOO close to bein' a downer!
This is a celebration, right!? Celebrate!

C'mon... Yusuke! You, me! Soda chugging
contest! Now!
Um... I don't know if we're ready for that...

Such idiocy... To think you could consume
more than I!
Hey, you better not spill any of that!
You idiots! You got soda all over my fur!
*sigh* Not exactly the celebration I'd planned...
